=== CODE NOTES - Legend of Success Joe | Ashita no Joe Densetsu (Game ID 13598) ===
Cada bloco abaixo é uma note completa: copie o corpo para o Memory Inspector no endereço indicado e publique.

--- 0x0000 ---
[Notes] Set created with cruncheevos scripts, maintained at:
https://github.com/vagnercruz/RAScripts/tree/main/Arcade/ashita-no-joe
Addresses below use the FBNeo mapping: RA address = 68K address - 0x100000.

--- 0x01a5 ---
[8-bit BCD] Credits
Value matches the on-screen CREDITS counter (BCD: 0x58 = "58").
+1 per coin inserted, -1 when a credit is consumed (game start / continue).
Display-only copies exist at 0xf248/0xf289 - they freeze outside the
title screen, do NOT use them for logic. This is the live counter.

--- 0x0304 ---
[8-bit] Stage / opponent ID
0x00 = Toko Reformatory (street brawl)
0x01 = Shohei Inagaki (ring)
0x02 = Wolf Kanagushi (street - backstage brawl with his bodyguards)
0x03 = Toru Rikiishi (ring)
0x04 = Gondo / The Ruffian (street)
0x05 = Tiger Ozaki (ring)
0x06 = Carlos Rivera (street)
0x07 = Kin Ryuhi (ring)
0x08 = Harimao (street - airport brawl)
0x09 = Jose Mendoza (ring)
0x0a = Ending / credits roll
0xff = Title screen / attract
Increments exactly on stage clear - Delta/Mem transition X -> X+1 is the
"completed stage X" signal used by all progression achievements.
Ring matches = odd values (01/03/05/07/09); street fights = even (00-08).

--- 0x0320 ---
[8-bit] P1 animation state (frame-by-frame)
WARNING: NOT reliable as a semantic flag. Values are reused across
contexts: 0x00 = fight intro AND lying down after a knockdown (frozen);
0x15 = falling AND also appears at the start of fights.
Kept documented to save future devs from the trap. For knockdown
detection use 0x0362 bar-boundary crossings instead.

--- 0x0346 ---
[8-bit] P1 active NORMAL punch ID
0x00 = none / 0x02 = hook (confirmed; other normal punches use other values)
Set while a normal (single A) punch is active; cleared shortly after
the punch resolves. Power punches use 0x0347 instead.

--- 0x0347 ---
[8-bit] P1 active POWER punch ID (A+B punches)
0x00 = none / 0x01 = Power Uppercut (confirmed)
Other Power punches (Power Straight/Hook/Body Blow) use other values.
Cleared right on/after the impact frame - achievement logic must accept
Mem OR Delta when reading it at a hit event ("Tomorrow's Fight").

--- 0x0362 ---
[8-bit] P1 total energy - all 3 bars in one value (mirror at 0x0364)
0x78 = full. Bars are NOT equal thirds; boundaries at 0x48 and 0x20
(bar sizes 48/40/32 units - Joe gets more fragile as he takes beatings).
A knockdown happens when the value crosses a boundary, and it snaps
exactly to 0x48 (1st), 0x20 (2nd), 0x00 (3rd = final KO / credit lost).
Knockdown detection: Delta > boundary AND Mem <= boundary, one frame.
Between fights a partially-drained bar refills to the top of the current
bar; fully lost bars never come back within the same credit.

--- 0x0364 ---
[8-bit] P1 total energy - display mirror of 0x0362
Use 0x0362 for logic.

--- 0x0368 ---
[8-bit BCD] Match timer - SECONDS (counts UP from 0:00 each fight)
BCD: on-screen "42" is stored as 0x42. Tens rollover 0x59 -> minute+1.
Minutes are at 0x0369. Timer resets at the start of every stage.

--- 0x0369 ---
[8-bit] Match timer - MINUTES (counts UP, starts at 0 each fight)
0x00 while less than one minute has elapsed - this is the whole logic
of "Lightning Knockout" (win with minutes still 0 = under 60 seconds).

--- 0x0384 ---
[16-bit] P1 Score / 100 (mirror at 0x0388)
Plain binary, NOT BCD. Displayed score = value x 100
(e.g. 146 = 14,600 pts; 1000 = 100,000 pts).
Resets to 0 on continue and on new game - a high score is inherently
a single-credit run, which naturally protects score achievements
against credit-feeding.

--- 0x0388 ---
[16-bit] P1 Score / 100 - display mirror of 0x0384
Use 0x0384 for logic.

--- 0x03e3 ---
[8-bit] Continue screen counter
0x00 = no continue screen shown this run.
+1 each time the continue countdown screen appears.
Resets to 0 on game over (letting the countdown expire) and on reset.
0x00 at the moment of beating Jose Mendoza = 1CC run
("Completely White Ashes").

--- 0x0462 ---
[8-bit] Opponent total energy (mirror at 0x0464)
Same structure as P1 (0x78 full, snaps to 0x48/0x20 on knockdowns).
0x00 = final KO - the frame Delta > 0 AND Mem == 0 is "the winning blow".
WARNING: entity slots are only stable in 1v1 ring matches. Street
stages spawn extra actors (bodyguards, pedestrians) and reallocate
slots - do not anchor logic on this address outside ring fights.

--- 0x0464 ---
[8-bit] Opponent total energy - display mirror of 0x0462
Use 0x0462 for logic.

--- 0x0566 ---
[8-bit] P1 attack class/phase data (paired with 0x0567)
WARNING: NOT a punch identifier. Values are shared between different
punches (hook and Power Uppercut read identical values here) and evolve
during the swing. Documented to prevent future misuse.
For punch identity use 0x0346 (normal) / 0x0347 (Power).

--- 0xf14c ---
[8-bit] Total coins inserted - machine bookkeeping (mirror at 0xf180)
Plain binary, lifetime count this session; unrelated to credits spent.

--- 0xf248 ---
[8-bit BCD] Credits - DISPLAY COPY (second copy at 0xf289)
WARNING: freezes when the credit display is not being redrawn
(e.g. during gameplay). Use 0x01a5 for logic.

--- 0xfdae ---
[8-bit] Game state (Neo Geo BIOS user mode)
0x00 = boot / init
0x01 = title screen / ATTRACT MODE / menus
0x02 = playing (real game; stays 0x02 through the ending)
The attract demo runs real gameplay under 0x01 - requiring 0x02 is the
set-wide demo protection. BIOS-owned: revalidate if the linked BIOS
ever changes (developed against MVS Asia/Europe ver. 3).
